ountries%20to%20follow%20suit%20and%20lead%20to%20a%20new%20arms%20race.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fexplainer-what-is-the-test-ban-treaty-and-why-would-a-country-conduct-a-nuclear-test%2Farticleshow%2F104702728.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fexplainer-what-is-the-test-ban-treaty-and-why-would-a-country-conduct-a-nuclear-test%2Famp_articleshow%2F104702728.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fexplainer-what-is-the-test-ban-treaty-and-why-would-a-country-conduct-a-nuclear-test%2Famp_articleshow%2F104702728.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Judges%20Must%20Not%20Take%20Case%20Unless%20Assigned%20By%20Chief%20Justice%3A%20Supreme%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EJudges%20have%20to%20follow%20discipline%20and%20ought%20not%20to%20take%20up%20any%20case%20unless%20it%20is%20specifically%20assigned%20by%20the%20chief%20justice%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20said%20while%20dealing%20with%20an%20appeal%20challenging%20an%20order%20passed%20by%20the%20Rajasthan%20High%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EObserving%20that%20taking%20up%20a%20case%20not%20specifically%20assigned%20by%20the%20chief%20justice%20was%20an%20%26quot%3Bact%20of%20gross%20impropriety%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20top%20court%20wondered%20how%20a%20civil%20writ%20petition%20for%20clubbing%20First%20Information%20Reports%20(FIRs)%20could%20be%20entertained.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20bench%20of%20justices%20Abhay%20S%20Oka%20and%20Pankaj%20Mithal%20was%20hearing%20an%20appeal%20against%20the%20May%20order%20of%20the%20high%20court%20which%20had%20directed%20that%20no%20coercive%20steps%20shall%20be%20taken%20against%20three%20persons%20in%20connection%20with%20eight%20FIRs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20noted%20the%20three%20persons%20had%20first%20approached%20the%20high%20court%20seeking%20quashing%20of%20the%20FIRs%20but%20no%20interim%20relief%20was%20granted%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20noted%20thereafter%2C%20they%20filed%20a%20separate%20writ%20petition%20on%20the%20civil%20side%20for%20clubbing%20the%20eight%20FIRs%20and%20consolidating%20them%20into%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAppellant%20Ambalal%20Parihar%2C%20at%20whose%20instance%20six%20FIRs%20were%20registered%20against%20the%20three%20persons%2C%20claimed%20before%20the%20top%20court%20that%20the%20method%20of%20filing%20a%20civil%20writ%20petition%20was%20invented%20and%20it%20was%20done%20to%20avoid%20the%20roster%20judge%20who%20had%20not%20granted%20interim%20relief.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20classic%20case%20of%20forum%20hunting%20by%20the%20second%20to%20fourth%20respondents%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20observed%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BThus%2C%20this%20is%20a%20case%20of%20gross%20abuse%20of%20process%20of%20law.%26quot%3B%20It%20noted%20in%20the%20roster%20notified%20by%20the%20chief%20justice%2C%20there%20was%20a%20separate%20roster%20for%20criminal%20writ%20petitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20courts%20allow%20such%20sharp%20practices%2C%20the%20roster%20notified%20by%20the%20chief%20justice%20will%20have%20no%20meaning.%20The%20judges%20have%20to%20follow%20discipline%20and%20ought%20not%20to%20take%20up%20any%20case%20unless%20it%20is%20specifically%20assigned%20by%20the%20chief%20justice%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said%20in%20its%20October%2016%20verdict.%20It%20said%20a%20judge%20can%20take%20up%20a%20case%20provided%20either%20the%20cases%20of%20that%20category%20have%20been%20assigned%20to%20him%20as%20per%20the%20notified%20roster%20or%20the%20particular%20case%20was%20specifically%20assigned%20by%20the%20chief%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThough%20a%20civil%20writ%20petition%20was%20filed%2C%20the%20judge%20ought%20to%20have%20converted%20into%20a%20criminal%20writ%20petition%20which%20could%20have%20been%20placed%20only%20before%20the%20roster%20judge%20taking%20up%20criminal%20writ%20petitions%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20top%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20said%20it%20was%20sure%20that%20this%20conduct%20of%20the%20three%20litigants%20will%20be%20considered%20by%20the%20concerned%20court%20taking%20up%20petitions%20under%20section%20482%20of%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%20(CrPC)%20seeking%20quashing%20of%20the%20FIRs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20fit%20case%20where%20the%20second%20to%20fourth%20respondents%20must%20be%20saddled%20with%20costs.%20We%20quantify%20the%20costs%20amount%20at%20Rs%2050%2C000%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20they%20would%20pay%20the%20cost%20to%20the%20Rajasthan%20State%20Legal%20Services%20Authority%20within%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20allowing%20the%20appeal%2C%20the%20bench%20held%20that%20action%20of%20filing%20the%20civil%20writ%20petition%20was%20nothing%20but%20a%20%26quot%3Bgross%20abuse%20of%20process%20of%20law%26quot%3B%20and%20it%20was%20a%20classic%20case%20of%20forum%20hunting.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20direct%20the%20registrar%20(judicial)%20of%20the%20Rajasthan%20High%20Court%20to%20place%20a%20copy%20of%20this%20order%20in%20all%20eight%20petitions%20under%20section%20482%20of%20CrPC%20filed%20by%20the%20second%20to%20fourth%20respondents%20for%20quashing%20First%20Information%20Reports%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3Cbr%3E%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698239700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-02%2Fa1ooga8_supreme-court-of-india_650x400_14_February_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fjudges-must-not-take-up-case-unless-assigned-by-chief-justice-supreme-court-4512368%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%