ganizations%2C%20according%20to%20August%202023%20data%20from%20Russia's%20Federal%20Penitentiary%20Service.%20That's%20more%20than%20double%20what%20was%20reported%20in%202022%2C%20when%209%2C300%20prisoners%20were%20forced%20to%20work%2C%20according%20to%20the%20research%20and%20analytics%20firm%20Jamestown%20Foundation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20trends%20have%20been%20sparked%20by%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcurrencies%2Frussian-economy-record-worker-shortage-sanction-ukraine-war-labor-exodus-2023-4%5C%22%3Erecord%20workforce%20shortage%20in%20Russia%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20around%20a%20million%20Russians%20having%20fled%20the%20country%20to%20avoid%20fighting%20or%20escape%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcurrencies%2Frussia-economy-crash-ruble-imports-account-finance-putin-moscow-ukraine-2023-7%5C%22%3ERussia's%20difficult%20economic%20situation%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Russian%20economy%20is%20facing%20harsh%20structural%20challenges%2C%20including%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20qualified%20work%20force%2C%26quot%3B%20Jamestown%20senior%20fellow%20Sergey%20Sukhankin%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamestown.org%2Fprogram%2Fthe-rise-of-prison-labor-in-the-russian-economy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enote%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Monday.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Kremlin%20has%20sought%20to%20integrate%20prison%20labor%20with%20certain%20sectors%20of%20the%20domestic%20economy%20to%20solve%20this%20issue.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20use%20convict%20labor%20isn't%20new%20to%20Russia.%20The%20practice%20dates%20back%20to%20the%20Soviet%20era's%20%26quot%3BGulag%26quot%3B%20system%2C%20where%20convicts%20were%20assigned%20to%20work%20in%20the%20riskiest%20and%20most%20%26quot%3Blucrative%26quot%3B%20sectors%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union's%20economy%2C%20Sukhankin%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrison%20labor%20could%20e