20navigated%20six%20economic%20cycles%20in%20his%20career%2C%20giving%20him%20a%20good%20sense%20of%20what's%20happening%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20coming%20off%20the%20top%20and%20we're%20starting%20to%20go%20down%2C%20so%20that%20would%20say%20to%20me%20that%20next%20year%20perhaps%20is%20not%20so%20wonderful%2C%20but%20then%20you'll%20hit%20your%20bottom%20and%20then%20we'll%20go%20up%20again%2C%26quot%3B%C2%A0Schwarzman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20trend%20is%20up%20%E2%80%93%20but%20we're%20living%20in%20a%20post-pandemic%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20meaning%20it%20will%20take%20time%20to%20move%20past%20the%20pain%20of%20inflation%20and%20higher%20interest%20rates.%20He%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20a%20recession%20struck%20after%20the%20Arab-Israel%20war%20in%201973.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchwarzman%20argued%20that%20official%20inflation%20statistics%20were%20overstating%20the%20problem%2C%20as%20Blackstone's%20portfolio%20companies%20had%20virtually%20no%20increase%20in%20their%20input%20costs%20last%20quarter.%20He%20also%20noted%20that%20revenue%20growth%20has%20slowed%20but%20profits%20have%20swelled%20in%20many%20cases%2C%20even%20though%20workforce%20expansion%20has%20slowed%20dramatically.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20says%20to%20me%20that%20the%20Fed%20is%20actually%20having%20pretty%20good%20impact%20in%20terms%20of%20taking%20inflation%20out%20of%20the%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchwarzman%20also%20jabbed%20at%20people%20who%20work%20from%20home%2C%20saying%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstephen-schwarzman-accused-remote-workers-of-not-working-hard-2023-10%5C%22%3Edon't%20work%20as%20hard%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20complained%20the%20remote-working%20trend%20is%20threatening%20to%20lift%20vacancy%20rates%20in%20some%20office%20buildings%20to%2030%25%2C%20making%20them%20unviable.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20going%20to%20have%20a%20very%20bad%20ending.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%