%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Firans-khamenei-says-us-directing-israel-bombing-of-gaza%2Farticleshow%2F104700850.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Firans-khamenei-says-us-directing-israel-bombing-of-gaza%2Famp_articleshow%2F104700850.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Firans-khamenei-says-us-directing-israel-bombing-of-gaza%2Famp_articleshow%2F104700850.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Powerful%20senators%20fire%20off%20letter%20decrying%20'abusive'%20tactics%20in%20Corizon%20bankruptcy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224224%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sen.%20Dick%20Durban%20and%20Sen.%20Elizabeth%20Warren%20address%20a%20town%20hall%20event.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6536dbd096f7540cd0636f0d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223168%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESenators%20Dick%20Durbin%20and%20Elizabeth%20Warren%20sent%20a%20letter%20raising%20%26quot%3Bserious%20questions%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20bankruptcy%20of%20prison%20health%20provider%20Corizon.%3Cp%3ENancy%20Lane%2FMediaNews%20Group%2FBoston%20Herald%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3ENine%20US%20senators%20including%20Elizabeth%20Warren%2C%20Dick%20Durbin%2C%20and%20Bernie%20Sanders%20have%20sent%20a%20letter%20to%20Corizon%20leaders%20demanding%20answers%20on%20its%20bankruptcy.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20letter%20says%20Corizon%20has%20sought%20%26quot%3Bto%20manipulate%20bankruptcy%20law%26quot%3B%20and%20calls%20the%20strategy%20%26quot%3Babusive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ECiting%20Insider's%20reporting%2C%20the%20senators%20gave%20Corizon%20two%20weeks%20to%20turn%20over%20details%20about%20its%20use%20of%20the%20Texas%20Two-Step%20to%20shield%20assets%20from%20creditors.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20powerful%20group%20of%20senators%20have%20pressed%20for%20answers%20about%20the%20bankruptcy%20of%20the%20private%20prison%20healthcare%20provider%20formerly%20known%20as%20Corizon%20Health.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.warren.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2F2023.10.24%2520Letter%2520re%2520Corizon%2520Texas%2520Two-Step.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%20sent%20Tuesday%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20executives%20of%20Corizon's%20successor%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20YesCare%20and%20Tehum%20Care%20Services%20%E2%80%94%20the%20lawmakers%20say%20Corizon%20employed%20an%20%26quot%3Babusive%26quot%3B%20bankruptcy%20strategy%20to%20avoid%20paying%20not%20just%20medical-malpractice%20lawsuits%20but%20also%20%26quot%3Bbills%20for%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars'%20worth%20of%20goods%20and%20services%20provided%20to%20Corizon%20by%20hospitals%2C%20small%20businesses%2C%20and%20your%20own%20former%20employees.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20nine%20senators%20include%20Elizabeth%20Warren%2C%20Bernie%20Sanders%2C%20Cory%20Booker%2C%20Judiciary%20Committee%20chair%20Dick%20Durbin%2C%20and%20Finance%20Committee%20chair%20Ron%20Wyden.%20They%20raise%20questions%20in%20the%20seven-page%20letter%20about%20the%20company's%20%26quot%3Blargely%20anonymous%20investors%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company's%20%26quot%3Bobfuscation%20of%20its%20ownership%20structure%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20assets%20it%20has%20transferred%20to%20%26quot%3Baffiliated%20entities%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20its%20attempts%20to%20escape%20liability%20for%20hundreds%20of%20medical-malpractice%20lawsuits%20filed%20by%20current%20and%20former%20prisoners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20bankruptcy%20system%20has%20many%20aims%2C%20but%20it%20was%20not%20designed%20to%20provide%20an%20avenue%20for%20companies%20to%20evade%20accountability%20for%20wrongdoing%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawmakers%20write.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETehum%20filed%20for%20bankruptcy%20in%20February%20%E2%80%94%20the%20final%20step%20in%20a%20controversial%20legal%20maneuver%20in%20which%20Corizon%20moved%20to%20Texas%20and%20split%20in%20two.%20As%20a%20result%20of%20the%20tactic%2C%20dubbed%20the%20Texas%20Two-Step%2C%20one%20company%2C%20called%20YesCare%2C%20got%20all%20of%20Corizon's%20corrections%20contracts%20while%20the%20other%2C%20Tehum%2C%20was%20saddled%20with%20Corizon's%20civil%20suits%20and%20most%20of%20its%20debt.%20Insider%20first%20reported%20on%20the%20company's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorizon-health-bankruptcy-yescare-texas-two-step-law-2023-8%5C%22%3Euse%20of%20the%20Two-Step%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20letter%2C%20addressed%20to%20YesCare%20CEO%20Jeffrey%20Sholey%20and%20Isaac%20Lefkowitz%2C%20Tehum's%20sole%20director%2C%20the%20senators%20blasted%20Corizon's%20attempt%20%26quot%3Bto%20manipulate%20bankruptcy%20law%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20skirting%20accountability%20for%20the%20harms%20that%20incarcerated%20individuals%20have%20endured%20under%20Corizon's%20care.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Texas%20Two-Step%20is%20a%20distorted%20use%20of%20the%20U.S.%20bankruptcy%20system%20by%20corporations%20to%20evade%20mass%20tort%20liability%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20senators%20write.%20%26quot%3BYour%20company%20has%20taken%20this%20abusive%20strategy%20a%20step%20farther.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawmakers%20urge%20Sholey%20and%20Lefkowitz%20to%20use%20%26quot%3Bthe%20full%20financial%20capabilities%26quot%3B%20of%20YesCare%2C%20Tehum%2C%20and%20other%20related%20entities%20to%20%26quot%3Bprovide%20full%20relief%20for%20meritorious%20claims%20against%20Corizon%20by%20all%20incarcerated%20people%2C%20their%20families%2C%20former%20employees%2C%20and%20third-party%20medical%20providers.%26quot%3B%20Those%20claims%20total%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprominent-bankruptcy-judge-recused-under-investigation-after-undisclosed-romantic-relationship-exposed-2023-10%5C%22%3E%241.2%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20Tehum%20is%20seeking%20to%20settle%20them%20for%20%2437%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20senators%20have%20given%20Tehum%20and%20YesCare%20two%20weeks%20to%20answer%20nine%20detailed%20questions%20about%20their%20leadership%2C%20ownership%20structure%2C%20corporate%20assets%2C%20affiliated%20entities%2C%20the%20civil%20suits%20against%20them%2C%20and%20the%20bankruptcy%20settlement%20negotiations%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20too%20long%2C%20corporations%20like%20Corizon%20have%20taken%20advantage%20of%20our%20bankruptcy%20system%2C%20engaging%20in%20maneuvers%20like%20the%20Texas%20Two-Step%20to%20hide%20from%20victims%20who%20deserve%20to%20be%20treated%20fairly%2C%26quot%3B%20Sen.%20Warren%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20calling%20for%20answers%20from%20Corizon.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESholey%2C%20Lefkowitz%2C%20YesCare%2C%20and%20Tehum%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorizon%20was%20once%20one%20of%20the%20nation's%20largest%20private%20prison%20healthcare%20providers%2C%20but%20claims%20of%20malpractice%20and%20patient%20neglect%20had%20been%20mounting%20against%20it%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222222%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20curved%20exterior%20of%20the%20Do%C3%B1a%20Ana%20County%20Detention%20Center%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6536e13a96908fd7cdb59f79%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Do%C3%B1a%20Ana%20County%20Detention%20Center%20in%20Las%20Cruces%2C%20New%20Mexico%2C%20where%20Hector%20Garcia%20spent%20his%20final%20days%20under%20Corizon's%20care.%3Cp%3EAdria%20Malcom%20for%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20senators%20excoriate%20Corizon%20for%20its%20repeated%20failure%20to%20provide%20adequate%20healthcare%20to%20prisoners%2C%20itemizing%20what%20they%20describe%20as%20%26quot%3Bglaring%20instances%20of%20neglect.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20specifically%20mentions%20the%20case%20of%20Hector%20Garcia%2C%20a%20father%20of%20four%20who%20died%20three%20days%20into%20a%20six-day%20sentence%20at%20a%20New%20Mexico%20jail%2C%20a%20case%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorizon-health-bankruptcy-yescare-texas-two-step-law-2023-8%5C%22%3EInsider%20profiled%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20letter%20says%20%26quot%3BCorizon%20providers%20ignored%20complaints%20of%20intense%20pain%20caused%20by%20an%20entirely%20treatable%20existing%20condition%20providers%20should%20have%20been%20aware%20of.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20his%20son%20Hector%20Garcia%20Jr.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorizon-health-bankruptcy-yescare-texas-two-step-law-2023-8%5C%22%3Etold%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20like%20he%20had%20a%20chance%20to%20call%20an%20ambulance%20himself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Unknown%20investors%20and%20associates'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawmakers'%20letter%20criticizes%20Corizon's%20use%20of%20the%20Texas%20Two-Step%20%26quot%3Bto%20pay%20pennies%20on%20the%20dollar%20to%20claimants%20that%20deserve%20recompense%20for%20poor%20health%20outcomes.%26quot%3B%20And%20it%20says%20serious%20questions%20remain%20about%20the%20opaque%20ownership%20behind%20YesCare%20and%20Tehum%2C%20issues%20first%20raised%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorizon-health-bankruptcy-yescare-texas-two-step-law-2023-8%5C%22%3EInsider's%20reporting%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BReporting%20suggests%20that%20the%20largely%20unknown%20investors%20and%20associates%20that%20spearheaded%20the%20Texas%20Two-Step%20have%20engaged%20in%20questionable%20and%20unjust%20tactics%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20letter%20says.%20%26quot%3BThis%20misuse%20of%20the%20bankruptcy%20system%20is%20unacceptable%2C%20and%20we%20are%20concerned%20that%20it%20may%20result%20in%20the%20denial%20of%20hundreds%20of%20claims%20stemming%20from%20the%20substandard%20care%20incarcerated%20people%20have%20received%20under%20Corizon's%20watch.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWarren%20had%20already%20expressed%20concern%20about%20one%20company%20affiliate.%20In%20January%202021%2C%20she%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.warren.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2F2020.01.27%2520Letter%2520to%2520Genesis%2520Healthcare%2520CEO%2520re%2520Bonuses%2520for%2520Top%2520Executives.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esent%20a%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20national%20nursing%20home%20chain%20Genesis%20Healthcare%2C%20questioning%20why%20the%20company%20had%20paid%20top%20executives%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20bonuses%20even%20though%20it%20had%20received%20%24300%20million%20in%20government%20aid%20and%20more%20than%202%2C800%20residents%20died%20on%20its%20watch%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23911031-yescares-alabama-department-of-corrections-program-proposal%23document%2Fp17%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20Alabama%20bid%20document%3C%2Fa%3E%20obtained%20by%20Insider%2C%20YesCare%20is%20managed%20and%20financially%20supported%20by%20Geneva%20Consulting%20LLC%2C%20a%20wholly%20owned%20subsidiary%20of%20Genesis.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELefkowitz%2C%20the%20sole%20director%20of%20Tehum%2C%20is%20now%20also%20a%20director%20at%20Genesis.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bid%20says%20YesCare%20entered%20into%20a%20management%20service%20agreement%20with%20Geneva%20Consulting%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20relationship%20between%20the%20two%20companies%20caught%20the%20senators'%20attention.%20They%20write%20that%20evidence%20suggests%20%26quot%3BYesCare%20may%20in%20fact%20be%20owned%20by%20Geneva%20Consulting%20or%20its%20parent%2C%20the%20nursing%20home%20giant%20Genesis%20HealthCare%20Inc.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCorizon's%20obfuscation%20of%20its%20ownership%20structure%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20write%2C%20%26quot%3Bheightens%20our%20concern%20that%20the%20company%20is%20attempting%20to%20evade%20liability.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnconvincing%20claims%20of%20'corporate%20separateness'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUntil%20recently%2C%20the%20bankruptcy%20looked%20to%20be%20on%20its%20way%20to%20a%20swift%20conclusion.%20Tehum%20and%20its%20largest%20creditors%20had%20submitted%20a%20joint%20bankruptcy%20plan%20proposing%20the%20%2437%20million%20settlement%2C%20which%20would%20have%20given%20current%20and%20former%20incarcerated%20patients%20just%20%245%2C000%20apiece%20for%20their%20medical-malpractice%20claims%20%E2%80%94%20even%20in%20cases%20where%20prisoners%C2%A0under%20Corizon's%20care.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20the%20judge%20who%20oversaw%20the%20settlement%20talks%2C%20David%20Jones%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbankruptcy-judge-david-jones-resigns-texas-corizon-2023-10%5C%22%3Esuddenly%20resigned%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20Insider%20published%20allegations%20that%20he%20was%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprison-health-provider-corizon-bankruptcy-clouded-by-judge-romantic-relationship-2023-10%5C%22%3Ean%20undisclosed%20romantic%20relationship%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20an%20attorney%20who%20represented%20YesCare%20in%20the%20negotiations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20US%20Trustee%20Program%2C%20in%20charge%20of%20watching%20over%20the%20integrity%20of%20the%20bankruptcy%20system%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprominent-bankruptcy-judge-recused-under-investigation-after-undisclosed-romantic-relationship-exposed-2023-10%5C%22%3Efiled%20an%20objection%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20bankruptcy%20court%2C%20citing%20Jones'%20involvement%20in%20the%20mediation%20and%20other%20concerns.%20In%20the%20latest%20blow%2C%20Christopher%20Lopez%2C%20the%20federal%20bankruptcy%20judge%20overseeing%20the%20case%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorizon-tehum-yescare-bankruptcy-deal-on-hold-2023-10%5C%22%3Esaid%20at%20a%20hearing%20last%20week%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20creditors%20needed%20more%20time%20to%20review%20the%20settlement%20%E2%80%94%20rejecting%20attempts%20by%20Tehum's%20attorneys%20to%20expedite%20approval.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20the%20company%20has%20attempted%20to%20wall%20off%20YesCare's%20assets%20from%20Tehum's%20creditors%2C%20claiming%20that%20the%20two%20companies%20are%20separate.%20The%20senators%20forcefully%20pushed%20back%20on%20that%20in%20the%20letter%2C%20writing%20that%20claims%20of%20%26quot%3Bcorporate%20separateness%26quot%3B%20are%20%26quot%3Ba%20transparent%20and%20unconvincing%20attempt%20to%20avoid%20adequately%20compensating%20victims.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWarren%20and%20Durbin%20have%20taken%20a%20hard%20line%20on%20the%20Texas%20Two-Step%2C%20which%20was%20attempted%20most%20famously%20by%20Johnson%20%26amp%3B%20Johnson%20to%20try%20to%20shed%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20talc-powder%20lawsuits.%20Five%20of%20the%20signers%20of%20Tuesday's%20letter%20are%20members%20of%20the%20Senate%20Judiciary%20Committee%2C%20which%20held%20a%20hearing%20last%20month%20on%20the%20Two-Step%20with%20the%20sharply%20worded%20title%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.judiciary.senate.gov%2Fcommittee-activity%2Fhearings%2Fevading-accountability-corporate-manipulation-of-chapter-11-bankruptcy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEvading%20Accountability%3A%20Corporate%20Manipulation%20of%20Chapter%2011%20Bankruptcy%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202021%2C%20Warren%20introduced%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.congress.gov%2Fbill%2F117th-congress%2F