0government%20bonds%20have%20declined%20steadily%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20hitting%20the%20lowest%20levels%20since%202009%20this%20summer.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EBut%20that%20doesn't%20necessarily%20mean%20Beijing%20is%20deliberately%20shifting%20away%20from%20dollar%20assets%2C%20according%20to%20strategists%20at%20Lloyds%20Bank.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20drop%20in%20UST%20holdings%20reflects%20other%20factors%20such%20as%20valuation%20changes%2C%20diversification%20into%20agency%20debt%20and%20China's%20efforts%20to%20stabilize%20its%20currency%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20holdings%20of%20US%20government%20bonds%20recently%20hit%20a%2014-year%20low.%20The%20No.%202%20foreign%20owner%20of%20Treasurys%20has%20been%20steadily%20trimming%20its%20portfolio%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimultaneously%2C%20the%20Asian%20nation%20has%20also%20been%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20an%20international%20movement%20%E2%80%94%20known%20as%20de-dollarization%20%E2%80%94%20to%20reduce%20reliance%20on%20the%20greenback%20in%20cross-border%20trade%20and%20investment%20flows%2C%20amid%20concern%20Washington%20could%20%26quot%3Bweaponize%26quot%3B%20the%20greenback's%20dominance%20to%20impose%20economic%20sanctions.%20Such%20fears%20have%20grown%20after%20the%20US%20slapped%20embargoes%20on%20Russia%20and%20Iran%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPredictably%2C%20financial%20markets%20have%20been%20rife%20with%20speculation%20in%20recent%20months%20that%20Beijing%20is%20calculatedly%20cutting%20back%20investments%20in%20US%20bonds%20to%20undermine%20the%20dollar%20and%20dent%20the%20pre-eminence%20of%20Treasuries%20as%20the%20most%20reliable%20asset%20class%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that's%20a%20mere%20myth%2C%20according%20to%20at%20least%20expert.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20China's%20holdings%20of%20Treasuries%20have%20indeed%20fallen%20by%20some%20%24220%20billion%20since%20the%20end%20of%202021%2C%20the%20reality%20is%20more%20nuance