%2F104695652.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Meta%20Sued%20In%20US%20For%20%26quot%3BDamaging%20Children's%20Health%26quot%3B%3A%20What%20Lawsuit%20Says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDozens%20of%20US%20states%20have%20accused%20Facebook%20and%20Instagram%20owner%20Meta%20of%20profiting%20%26quot%3Bfrom%20children's%20pain%2C%26quot%3B%20damaging%20their%20mental%20health%20and%20misleading%20people%20about%20the%20safety%20of%20its%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20suit%2C%20filed%20in%20the%20federal%20court%20in%20Oakland%2C%20California%2C%20adds%20to%20growing%20scrutiny%20of%20social%20media%20giants%20over%20how%20they%20serve%20their%20youngest%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Suit%20Demands%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20total%2C%20more%20than%2040%20US%20states%20are%20suing%20Meta%2C%20though%20some%20opted%20to%20file%20in%20local%20courts%20rather%20than%20join%20in%20the%20federal%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20suit%20accuses%20Meta%20of%20deceptive%20and%20unlawful%20conduct%2C%20harming%20vulnerable%20youth%20for%20financial%20gain.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20states%20are%20seeking%20a%20court%20order%20directing%20Meta%20to%20cease%20the%20practices%20at%20issue%20and%20imposing%20civil%20fines%20for%20each%20alleged%20violation%20of%20state%20and%20federal%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20legal%20filing%20argues%20that%20Meta%20has%20%26quot%3Bexploited%26quot%3B%20young%20users%20by%20creating%20a%20business%20model%20designed%20to%20maximize%20time%20they%20spend%20on%20the%20platform%20despite%20harm%20to%20their%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Made%20US%20States%20Sue%20Meta%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20that%20social%20media%20companies%20shoulder%20responsibility%20for%20the%20potential%20damage%20their%20products%20cause%20to%20young%20people%20came%20to%20the%20fore%20late%20in%202021%20when%20former%20Meta%20employee%20Frances%20Haugen%20emerged%20as%20a%20whistleblower%20with%20documents%20about%20internal%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20investigation%20was%20launched%20after%20Facebook%20whistleblower%20Frances%20Haugen%20leaked%20more%20than%2020%2C000%20pages%20of%20internal%20documents%20that%20sparked%20criticism%20that%20the%20social%20media%20giant%20had%20put%20profit%20before%20the%20security%20of%20its%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20testimony%20to%20American%20and%20European%20lawmakers%20in%202021%2C%20she%20insisted%20that%20Facebook%20failed%20to%20curtail%20toxic%20content%20and%20that%20the%20company%20cannot%20be%20trusted%20to%20change%20its%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFacebook%20later%20that%20year%20changed%20its%20name%20to%20Meta%20in%20a%20move%20critics%20suspected%20was%20intended%20to%20distance%20the%20company%20from%20its%20social%20networking%20controversies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Meta%20Says%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeta%20said%20it's%20committed%20to%20keeping%20teens%20safe%20online%20and%20has%20introduced%20more%20than%2030%20tools%20to%20support%20youths%20and%20their%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20firm%20said%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bdisappointed%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20suit%20and%20that%20the%20states%20were%20not%20working%20with%20the%20array%20of%20social%20media%20companies%20to%20create%20age-appropriate%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20maintained%20that%20it%20has%20developed%20more%20than%2030%20tools%20in%20its%20apps%20to%20support%20teenage%20users%2C%20and%20made%20it%20easier%20for%20parents%20to%20%26quot%3Bshape%26quot%3B%20online%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeta%20contended%20that%20the%20attorneys%20generals%20have%20singled%20out%20the%20firm%20instead%20of%20seeking%20industry-wide%20solutions%20given%20the%20popularity%20of%20rivals%20including%20TikTok%2C%20YouTube%20and%20Snap.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698226740000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-06%2Fe50rkdd